In the practice of measuring the size of US [[commercial broadcasting]] and [[newspaper]] audiences, '''cume''', short for "cumulative audience", is a measure of the total number of unique consumers over a specified period.
The technical definition of cume is restricted by [[Arbitron]], which is now referred to as Nielsen Audio, as requiring a listener to tune in for at least five minutes.<ref>{{cite web | title = Terms for the Trade | publisher = Arbitron | url = http://www.arbitron.com/radio_stations/tradeterms.htm | accessdate = 2008-06-30}}</ref>
